Introduction

Kwak Young Min, popularly known as Aron, is a Korean-American singer, rapper, and DJ. In 2012, he debuted as the sub-vocalist and sub-rapper of the boy group NU'EST under Pledis Entertainment. He is the group's eldest member and representative when it comes to speaking in English.

On February 28, 2022, Pledis Entertainment announced that the NU'EST members' contracts will expire on March 14 and Aron decided not to renew with the company.
